member.remarks:
The Add action can be used when a LookupSource is set on a Query. This action allows the user to add existing entities to the current Query, current entities will be filtered from the LookupSource.
The parent entity can be loaded by using the Context property and calling the GetEntity method on it, e.g. Person parentPerson = Context.GetEntity<Person>(parent, true);
The entities can then be added one by one, e.g. entities.Run(e => parentPerson.Collection.Add(e));
The changes can then be saved by calling .

The Delete action is available when the current user has the Delete right for the Persistent Object. This action will be changed to a Remove action in a Query if the relation isnt required.
The OnDelete base method will call MarkForDeletion for each entity, and then save these changes.
entities.Where(e => e != null).Run(MarkForDeletion);
PersistChanges();

remarks.code:
var obj = e.PersistentObject;
obj.Attributes = e.ChangedAttributes;

foreach (var id in e.BulkObjectIds)
{
    obj.ObjectId = id;
    OnSave(obj);

    if (obj.HasError)
        break;
}

member.remarks:
The action will be invoked when a user opens an item in a Query, or when there is a ProgramUnitItem that is linked to a Persistent Object. This will only be available if the user has the Read right for the Persistent Object.
The base implementation will call the LoadEntity method that will return an entity for the Persistent Object, e.g. Person person = LoadEntity(obj);
This entity will then be used to load all the values of the attributes, e.g. obj.PopulateAttributeValues(person, true);
When you do not call the base implementation,  could be used to assign the correct attribute values from the loaded entity.

